node.title: Live - Latest COVID update incoming, including case in Northland's Hokianga
node.content: ["The latest COVID-19 update is incoming, including how many new community cases of the virus have been reported in New Zealand and how many - likely Omicron - at the border.", "There were 27 new community cases reported on Monday and 33 in MIQ. We already know of one new case that will be recorded in Tuesday's numbers, a Northland person in the Hokianga area.", "\"This case is linked to a known case in the Hokianga and was already in isolation as a close contact when they tested positive,\" the Ministry of Health said on Monday. \"Further investigations are underway to confirm any potential exposures from this case.\"", "There were 27 new community cases announced on Monday and 33 at the border.", "Thirty-five people are in hospital, including one in ICU or HDU.", "One new case has been found in Northland, but will be included in Tuesday's numbers.", "There are no new cases linked to the drum and bass festival earlier in January.", "The Wellington case attended the Britomart Block Party on New Year's Eve in Auckland.", "More than half a million doses of the paediatric Pfizer vaccine have arrived in New Zealand for children aged 5 to 11 years old.", "Click here for locations of interest.", "11:20am - Kia ora, good morning and welcome to Newshub's live updates for Tuesday.", "We are awaiting the latest case update from the Ministry of Health, but one case mentioned by the ministry on Monday will be counted on Tuesday.", "\"There is one new case to announce in Northland today \u2013 in the Hokianga area,\" the ministry said on Monday.", "\"This case was reported after the daily cut-off and will be included in tomorrow\u2019s figures.", "\"This case is linked to a known case in the Hokianga and was already in isolation as a close contact when they tested positive. Further investigations are underway to confirm any potential exposures from this case.\""]
